title: Dune Official Trailer
description: Beyond fear, destiny awaits. Watch the trailer for the highly anticipated #DuneMovie now. -----------------https://www.facebook.com/dune https://twitter.com/dunemoviehttps://www.instagram.com/dunemovie-----------------Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049‚Äù)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù  ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson  (‚ÄúStephen  King‚Äôs  Doctor  Sleep,‚Äù   ‚ÄúMission:  Impossible  ‚Äì  Fallout‚Äù),  Oscar  Isaac  (the ‚ÄúStar  Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr.  Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragon‚Äù),    David  Dastmalchian  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Dark  Knight‚Äù), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,‚Äù  Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex  Education‚Äù),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).   Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W.  Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. Behind  the  scenes,  Villeneuve  reteamed  with  two-time  Oscar-nominated  production  designer  Patrice  Vermette  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Young  Victoria‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-nominated  editor  Joe  Walker  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚Äú12  Years  a  Slave‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-winning  visual  effects  supervisor  Paul  Lambert  (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù).    He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù  ‚ÄúZero  Dark  Thirty,‚Äù  ‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story‚Äù);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù  ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.
